Defendant Sherri A McFarland in court with attorney Jeremy J Guza.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 15.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 15:
- Total sentence: 2 years (Initial Confinement: 1 year, Extended Supervision: 1 year)  Stayed for 1 year Probation
- Defendant IS eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- DNA Surcharge waived
- Conditions of  Probation:  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. No drug paraphernalia. Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed; Inform Agent of all prescriptions. Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling.  No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged or distributed. No contact with any victims - Walgreens or CVS Pharmacies or co-defendant's or any other witnesses identified in the complaint.   
- Defendant to perform 70 hours of community service as a Condition of Probation.
- 10 days jail Condition Time (nonworking hours) STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion. Huber/Straight time to be used at the Agents discretion.
